                     <interp inst="t17780603-9-person102" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>On Thursday morning, the 14th of May, I saw the prisoner's legs coming out of Mr. Richardson's window; I overtook him twenty or thirty yards from the house; I took him by the collar, and found these two weights upon him; he begged I would let him go, and he would never do so any more.</p>
               <p>[The weights were produced in court, and deposed to by the prosecutor.]</p>
               <p>PRISONER's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>That gentleman has known me twenty-five years, and never knew me wrong man, woman, or child before; I was not in the shop; I have a wife and four children.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17780603-9-verdict45" type="verdictDescription">
